12 Section 1. Section 3-10-601, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "3-10-601. Collection and disposition of fines, penalties, forfeitures, and fees. (1) Except as
14 provided in 61-8-726 and 75-7-123, a justice's court shall collect the fees prescribed by law for justices' courts
15 and shall pay them into the county treasury of the county in which the justice of the peace holds office, on or
16 before the 10th day of each month, to be credited to the general fund of the county.
17 (2) Except as provided in 61-8-726, 75-7-123, and subsection (4) of this section, all fines,
18 penalties, and forfeitures that are required to be imposed, collected, or paid in a justice's court must, for each
19 calendar month, be paid by the justice's court on or before the 5th day of the following month to the treasurer of
20 the county in which the justice's court is situated, except that they may be distributed as provided in 44-12-213
21 if imposed, collected, or paid for a violation of Title 45, chapter 9 or 10.
22 (3) Except as provided in 46-18-236(7), and 61-8-726, and 75-7-123, the county treasurer shall, as
23 provided in 15-1-504, distribute money received under subsection (2) as follows:
24 (a) 50% to the department of revenue for deposit in the state general fund; and
25 (b) 50% to the county general fund.
26 (4) (a) The justice's court may contract with a private person or entity for the collection of any final
27 judgment that requires a payment to the justice's court.
